history.content:
Due to COVID-19, the class will be online. The plans are still fluid (I haven't finalized things yet) but this is the current plan:

  • There will still be three projects, which will be in groups of 4 as usual.
  • There may be fewer homeworks since we only have 8 weeks for the class.
  • I might do weekly quizzes instead of a few large exams given the online format.

Source: I'm the summer instructor for CS 162.

Does anyone know if there is any difference between taking 162 over the summer versus taking it during fall/spring? Is it important to find a good group for that class, or is it possible to solo projects? Also, does 162 helps with recruiting for SWE positions?
